{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871143074,"sessionID":"ses_285d6b53effe7tM0u5fWyHkJ28","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2b2c77001xzrCp7z2HR1lkS","messageID":"msg_d7a2a04e1001ShWdtM5x8rLVT3","sessionID":"ses_285d6b53effe7tM0u5fWyHkJ28","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-de07350bebf94582be63c4856de9d10c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","content":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-022 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `publish` command in AgentCube CLI to deploy agent containers to Kubernetes. The command orchestrates the entire publish lifecycle: preparing container images (Docker push or explicit URL), deploying to target infrastructure (AgentCube AgentRuntime CR or standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service), and updating metadata with deployment information.\n\n**Current State**: CLI has `pack` and `build` commands that generate Dockerfile and build container images, but no deployment capability. Users must manually push images and create Kubernetes resources.\n\n**Target State**: \n- Single `kubectl-agentcube publish` command that deploys agents to Kubernetes\n- Support for two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service)\n- Automatic image preparation via Docker push or explicit image URL\n- Metadata updated with deployment info, agent_id, and endpoint URLs\n- Namespace, replicas, and NodePort configuration support\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` class with publish orchestration logic |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | `publish` Typer command with CLI options |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for standard K8s Deployment/Service |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for AgentRuntime CR deployment |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Image push methods (extends AR-021) |\n\n### 2.2 PublishRuntime Methods\n\n| Method | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `publish(workspace_path, **options)` | Main orchestration entry point |\n| `_publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via AgentCube AgentRuntime CR |\n| `_publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, **options)` | Deploy via standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service |\n| `_prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Image preparation (push or URL) |\n| `_prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Push local Docker image to registry |\n| `_prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)` | Use cloud-built image URL |\n| `_update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)` | Persist deployment info to metadata YAML |\n\n### 2.3 CLI Options\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` / `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n| `--image-url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n| `--image-username` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n| `--image-password` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n| `--description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n| `--region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `--cloud-provider` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--provider` | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n| `--node-port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s |\n| `--replicas` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas (default: 1) |\n| `--namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `--verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n### 2.4 Out of Scope\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| Cloud publish implementation | Requires cloud provider SDK integration; placeholder only |\n| Helm chart deployment | Different deployment paradigm; future enhancement |\n| Auto-scaling configuration | Not specified in requirements; HPA would be separate feature |\n| Secret management | Beyond current scope; requires vault integration |\n| Multi-cluster deployment | Requires federation setup; future enhancement |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   └── publish_runtime.py     # PublishRuntime class\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py        # KubernetesProvider class\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py  # AgentCubeProvider class\n│   │   └── docker_service.py      # (extend with push_image)\n│   └── cli/\n│       └── main.py                # publish command (addition to existing)\n└── tests/\n    ├── test_publish_runtime.py    # Unit tests for PublishRuntime\n    ├── test_k8s_provider.py       # Unit tests for KubernetesProvider\n    └── test_agentcube_provider.py # Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider\n```\n\n### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Impact |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | Python client for Kubernetes API; optional dependency under `[k8s]` extras |\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push operations |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n| `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and table output |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n| `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for future cloud integration |\n\n### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Method Usage |\n|----------|--------------|\n| `invoke` command | Uses agent_endpoint from metadata for HTTP calls |\n| `status` command | Reads k8s_deployment info from metadata |\n| `pack`/`build` commands | Provide image info for publish flow |\n| Users | CLI invocation `kubectl-agentcube publish -f ./my-agent` |\n\n### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Metadata schema**: Adding `k8s_deployment` field with sub-fields (`type`, `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `service_url`, `agent_id`)\n- **Provider parameter**: New `--provider` flag changes behavior significantly\n- **AgentRuntime CR dependency**: Requires Volcano AgentCube CRD installed for `agentcube` provider\n- **Registry credentials**: Password passed via CLI flag (insecure); recommend env vars or secret files\n\n### 3.5 Compatibility Notes\n\n- Kubernetes client `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config()` reads from `~/.kube/config` by default\n- NodePort range must be 30000-32767 per Kubernetes specification\n- AgentRuntime CR uses API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- Image URL format: `{registry}/{repository}/{image}:{tag}`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: Direct kubectl Execution\n\n**Approach**: Generate YAML manifests and execute `kubectl apply` via `subprocess.run()`.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Familiar to K8s users; no Python SDK dependency |\n| Cons | No programmatic status checks; harder error parsing; platform-specific; no wait-for-ready logic |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Kubernetes Python SDK provides typed API, wait loops, and structured status retrieval.\n\n### Alternative 2: Helm Chart Publishing\n\n**Approach**: Package agent as Helm chart and use `helm install` for deployment.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Standard K8s packaging; templating support; versioning built-in |\n| Cons | Requires Helm CLI; additional complexity; not in original spec |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as alternative publishing mode in future.\n\n### Alternative 3: Separate Push and Deploy Commands\n\n**Approach**: Split into `push-image` and `deploy` commands instead of unified `publish`.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | More granular control; can push without deploying |\n| Cons | More commands to learn; friction in typical workflow |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Unified `publish` command matches spec requirements and provides smoother user experience.\n\n### Alternative 4: Docker Compose for Local Testing\n\n**Approach**: Support Docker Compose as deployment target for local development.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Easy local testing; no K8s required |\n| Cons | Different networking model; not production-ready |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Focus on Kubernetes deployment per spec; local testing via `docker run` sufficient.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Kubernetes cluster unreachable | Load kubeconfig first; fail early with clear error message |\n| AgentRuntime CRD not installed | `AgentCubeProvider` checks CR existence; raises `ValueError` if not found |\n| Missing router_url/workload_manager_url for agentcube | Validation in `_publish_cr_to_k8s` raises `ValueError` |\n| Image push auth failure | `DockerService._docker_login_sdk` handles credentials; log warning on failure |\n| Deployment timeout | `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready(timeout=120)` raises `TimeoutError` |\n| NodePort collision | K8s auto-assigns if NodePort not specified; validation for range 30000-32767 |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._ensure_namespace()` to create namespace if missing\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` for Deployment + Service creation\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_deployment()` with sanitization, env_vars\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._create_service()` with NodePort handling\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready()` with timeout loop\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` for pod/deployment status\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent()` for cleanup\n- [ ] Implement `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name()` for K8s name compliance\n- [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.__init__()` with namespace, kubeconfig options\n- [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._ensure_namespace()` \n- [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` for AgentRuntime CR\n- [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider._sanitize_name()` for CR name compliance\n- [ ] Implement `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()` for CR status retrieval\n- [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime.publish()` orchestration entry point\n- [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s()` for AgentCube provider\n- [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._publish_k8s()` for standard K8s provider\n- [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_image_for_publishing()` image preparation\n- [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` Docker push logic\n- [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._prepare_cloud_image()` cloud image URL handling\n- [ ] Implement `PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata()` metadata persistence\n- [ ] Add `publish` Typer command in `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- [ ] Add error handling with `_handle_error()` for verbose traceback\n- [ ] Add Rich `Progress` spinner for publish status\n- [ ] Add `k8s_deployment` and `agent_id` fields to `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n- [ ] Unit tests for KubernetesProvider mock K8s API\n- [ ] Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider mock CR API\n- [ ] Unit tests for image preparation logic\n- [ ] Integration test for full publish workflow (mocked)\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- Spec: `changes/AR-022/spec.md`\n- Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n- CLI Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: `publish` command\n- Deployment Spec: `deployment/spec.md` — Kubernetes deployment patterns\n- Python SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md` — AgentRuntimeClient integration\n- AR-021 — CLI build command (image preparation dependency)\n- Kubernetes Python Client: https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python\n- Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n- Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-022/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871143042,"end":1775871143072}}}}
